q{ Q:"Group with quantities not having same dimensions" A:"c" O:a)"Velocity, speed",b)"Pressure, stress",c)"Force, impulse",d)"Work, energy" R:"Force [MLTвҒ»ВІ], impulse [MLTвҒ»В№] different." }

q{ Q:"Percentage errors in mass 3%, speed 4%. Maximum error in KE is" A:"a" O:a)"11%",b)"10%",c)"8%",d)"9%" R:"KE = ВҪ mvВІ, fractional error = О”m/m + 2О”v/v = 3% + 2Г—4% = 11%." }

q{ Q:"Vector product of two vectors is zero when they are" A:"a" O:a)"Parallel",b)"Equal",c)"Perpendicular",d)"At 60В°" R:"sinОё=0 вҶ’ parallel." }

q{ Q:"In right hand rule, direction of product vector is" A:"a" O:a)"Along the thumb erect",b)"Perpendicular to erect thumb",c)"Along rotation of fingers",d)"None" R:"Thumb gives direction." }

q{ Q:"Object slides at constant speed down inclined plane, coefficient of friction approximately" A:"c" O:a)"sinОё",b)"cosОё",c)"tanОё",d)"cotОё" R:"Ој = tanОё." }

q{ Q:"Two forces 3N and 2N at angle Оё, resultant R. First force increased to 6N, resultant becomes 2R. Then Оё=" A:"d" O:a)"30В°",b)"60В°",c)"90В°",d)"120В°" R:"RВІ=9+4+12cosОё, (2R)ВІ=36+4+24cosОё вҶ’ 4RВІ=40+24cosОё. Substitute RВІ: 4(13+12cosОё)=40+24cosОё вҶ’ 52+48cosОё=40+24cosОё вҶ’ 12 = -24cosОё вҶ’ cosОё = -1/2 вҶ’ Оё=120В°." }

q{ Q:"Torque acting on a body determines" A:"c" O:a)"Acceleration",b)"Linear acceleration",c)"Angular acceleration",d)"Direction of motion" R:"П„ = I Оұ." }

q{ Q:"If velocity is uniform, velocity-time graph is a straight line" A:"a" O:a)"Parallel to x-axis",b)"Parallel to y-axis",c)"At 45В°",d)"Along y-axis" R:"Constant velocity вҶ’ horizontal line." }

q{ Q:"Angle of projection for maximum horizontal range" A:"b" O:a)"30В°",b)"45В°",c)"60В°",d)"90В°" R:"45В°." }

q{ Q:"Ratio of distances moved by freely falling body from rest in 4th and 5th second" A:"b" O:a)"4:5",b)"7:9",c)"16:25",d)"1:1" R:"Distance in nth second вҲқ (2n-1). 4th:7, 5th:9 вҶ’ 7:9." }

q{ Q:"According to relativity, fourth dimension added is" A:"d" O:a)"Space",b)"Inertial frame",c)"Speed of light",d)"Time" R:"Time." }

q{ Q:"Water falls from dam 19.6 m below, velocity at turbine (g=9.8)" A:"b" O:a)"9.8 m/s",b)"19.6 m/s",c)"39.2 m/s",d)"98 m/s" R:"v = вҲҡ(2gh)=вҲҡ(2Г—9.8Г—19.6)=вҲҡ(384.16)=19.6 m/s." }

q{ Q:"Escape velocity of Earth in km/s" A:"b" O:a)"9.75",b)"11.2",c)"12.3",d)"15.6" R:"11.2 km/s." }

q{ Q:"Which is constant for a satellite in orbit?" A:"c" O:a)"Velocity",b)"KE",c)"Angular momentum",d)"PE" R:"Angular momentum conserved (no external torque)." }

q{ Q:"Pump of 2 kW raises water in 1 minute to height 10 m. How much water? (g=10)" A:"b" O:a)"1000 liters",b)"1200 liters",c)"100 liters",d)"2000 liters" R:"Power = mgh/t вҶ’ 2000 = mГ—10Г—10/60 вҶ’ m = 2000Г—60/100 = 1200 kg = 1200 liters." }

q{ Q:"Escape velocity from Earth 11 km/s. Planet radius twice, same density. Escape velocity?" A:"a" O:a)"22 km/s",b)"11 km/s",c)"5.5 km/s",d)"16.5 km/s" R:"v вҲқ RвҲҡПҒ. Radius double вҶ’ v doubles вҶ’ 22 km/s." }

q{ Q:"If force and displacement in direction of force are doubled, work becomes" A:"b" O:a)"Double",b)"4 times",c)"Half",d)"вҲҡx times" R:"W = Fd вҶ’ both double вҶ’ 4 times." }

q{ Q:"Electric motor hauls cage 400 kg up 1200 m in 2 minutes, efficiency 80%. Power required?" A:"d" O:a)"3.2 kW",b)"5 kW",c)"32 kW",d)"50 kW" R:"Output power = mgh/t = 400Г—10Г—1200/120 = 40000 W = 40 kW. Input = output/0.8 = 50 kW." }

q{ Q:"A couple produces" A:"b" O:a)"Purely linear motion",b)"Purely rotational motion",c)"Linear and rotational",d)"No motion" R:"Pure torque." }

q{ Q:"Units of angular acceleration" A:"c" O:a)"Radian",b)"Radian/s",c)"Radian/sВІ",d)"None" R:"rad/sВІ." }

