q{ Q:"Laplace formula derived from" A:"b" O:a)"Isothermal",b)"Adiabatic",c)"Isobaric",d)"Isochoric" R:"Adiabatic." }

q{ Q:"In absence of external torque, angular momentum is" A:"a" O:a)"Constant",b)"Variable",c)"Unstable",d)"Zero" R:"Conserved." }

q{ Q:"Progressive waves 300 Hz, stationary waves with adjacent nodes 1.5 m apart. Speed?" A:"d" O:a)"100 m/s",b)"200 m/s",c)"450 m/s",d)"900 m/s" R:"Node spacing = О»/2 = 1.5 вҶ’ О»=3 m. v = fО» = 300Г—3 = 900 m/s." }

q{ Q:"Possible frequency of ultraviolet radiation" A:"d" O:a)"1Г—10^6 Hz",b)"1Г—10^9 Hz",c)"1Г—10^12 Hz",d)"1Г—10^15 Hz" R:"UV ~ 10^15 Hz." }

q{ Q:"Minimum distance for clear echo" A:"b" O:a)"10 m",b)"16.5 m",c)"33 m",d)"66 m" R:"About 17 m (persistence of hearing 0.1s, speed 330 m/s вҶ’ 33 m round trip, so 16.5 m one way)." }

q{ Q:"Which is not produced by sound in air?" A:"a" O:a)"Polarization",b)"Diffraction",c)"Refraction",d)"Reflection" R:"Sound is longitudinal, no polarization." }

q{ Q:"Conduction due to pair generation in semiconductor is" A:"b" O:a)"Polarity",b)"Intrinsic conduction",c)"Electrostatic",d)"Amplitude modulation" R:"Intrinsic." }

q{ Q:"Every point of a wave front may be considered as a" A:"c" O:a)"Source",b)"Source of wave front",c)"Source of secondary wave front",d)"None" R:"Huygens' principle." }

q{ Q:"Phenomenon of polarization occurs only in" A:"a" O:a)"Electromagnetic",b)"Longitudinal",c)"Mechanical",d)"Matter waves" R:"Transverse waves." }

