// Passage (Qs 176-180)
meta Subj1:"English"/Chap1:"Reading Comprehension"/Topi1:"Passage"/Type1:"U"/Diff1:"M"/Stem1:""

q{ Q:"The advent of science and technology has increased the" A:"c" O:a)"freedom of people",b)"tyranny of political parties",c)"powers of the government",d)"chances of economic inequality" R:"Passage: 'growth of government is a necessary result of growth of technology'." }

q{ Q:"A spirit of moderation on the economically sound people would make the less privileged" A:"d" O:a)"unhappy with the rich",b)"more interested in freedom and security",c)"unhappy with their lot",d)"clamour less for absolute equality" R:"Passage: 'spirit of self-denial... will greatly soften the demand for absolute equality'." }

q{ Q:"The growth of government is necessitated to" A:"c" O:a)"make rich and poor happy",b)"curb accumulation of wealth",c)"monitor science and technology",d)"deploy police force wisely" R:"Passage: 'necessary result of the growth of technology and its problems'." }

q{ Q:"'Era of good feeling' in second sentence refers to" A:"a" O:a)"time of prosperity",b)"time of adversity",c)"time without government",d)"time of police atrocities" R:"Implies a period of harmony/prosperity." }

q{ Q:"'Tolerable state of balance' means" A:"d" O:a)"adequate police force",b)"reasonable economic equality",c)"reasonable government interference",d)"reasonable check on economic power" R:"Passage: 'keeping economic factors in a tolerable state of balance'." }

// Analogies (Qs 181-185)
q{ Q:"race : fatigue ::" A:"a" O:a)"fasting : hunger",b)"round : boxing",c)"flower : colors",d)"hiking : gangrene" R:"Race causes fatigue; fasting causes hunger." }

q{ Q:"strut : walking ::" A:"d" O:a)"sweating : wrestling",b)"hunter : fire",c)"speech : stage",d)"stammer : talk" R:"Strut is a way of walking; stammer is a way of talking." }

q{ Q:"industries : hardworking ::" A:"b" O:a)"sky : blue",b)"muddy : unclear",c)"book : reading",d)"pond : lake" R:"Industries are hardworking? Actually not clear. Set b: muddy means unclear." }

q{ Q:"scholar : ignorant ::" A:"a" O:a)"hardworking : lazy",b)"knife : sword",c)"courage : bold",d)"luxury : wealth" R:"Scholar is opposite of ignorant; hardworking opposite of lazy." }

q{ Q:"cool : frozen ::" A:"b" O:a)"sharp : cut",b)"warm : hot",c)"hassock : stool",d)"freedom : liberty" R:"Increasing intensity: cool to frozen, warm to hot." }

// Synonyms and Antonyms (Qs 186-190)
